 from actors as individuals to shifting collective subjects, often operating under false identities; from a world made of sturdy print to one of frail instruments and mistranscribed manuscripts; from a complacent Europe to an emerging system of complex geopolitics and globalizing information systems; and from an epistemology based on the stolid problem of eternal truths to one generated through and in the service of playful, politically engaged, and cunning schemes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSciencevBiography. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aphilosophy, philosopher, astronomer, astronomy, space, planets, stars, well known, famous, gianfrancesco sagredo, politics, political, knowledge, intelligence, intellect, history, historical, academic, scholarly, research, biographical, 1500s, 1600s, scientist, scientific, science, archival, painting, woodcut, crime, letters, correspondence, primary source, critique.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226167022423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226167022/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles